This test checks BASE premium (just the sum of 2×25=50). To isolate from first-insurance/fee modifiers, we need a way to expose the base premium calculation. Two options:
(a) Test via quote with first-insurance disabled somehow
(b) Activate as a test that checks final premium with newcomer = base + 10% + fee = 50 + 5 + 5 = 60

Use option (b): test the FINAL premium for 2 runes as newcomer:
```ts
it("2 runes have base premium 50 G (no block, requires exactly 3)", () => {
  // base 50 + 10% first-ins (5) + 5 fee = 60
  expect(quote({ yearsWithMHPCO: 0 }, [
    { type: "rune" },
    { type: "rune" },
  ])).toBe(60);
});
```

Wait — first-insurance is "per item" with 10% on base. The 10% applies to each rune individually: 25*1.1 + 25*1.1 = 55. Then fee 5 = 60. So expect 60.

